					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There exists a "libunif" whose purpose was to simplify the creation and parsing of UNIF files, though it can be somewhat complex to deal with.
<br />For creation of them, I opted for a simpler approach - I wrote a small program, named <a href="http://qmt.ath.cx/~nes/tools/makeunif10.zip" class="postlink">MakeUNIF</a>, which takes a small textfile and creates a UNIF file based on the parameters inside. For .NES files, I made a similar utility named <a href="http://qmt.ath.cx/~nes/tools/makeines10.zip" class="postlink">MakeINES</a>.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
